while (getValueAtIndex(nrstSeqStartIndx * 2) < position) {
    nrstSeqStartIndx *=2;
}
while (getValueAtIndex(nrstSeqStartIndx +1) <= position) nrstSeqStartIndx++; Wait, the second loop is incrementing nrstSeqStartIndx until the next value (nrstSeqStartIndx+1) would be beyond the position. So after the first loop, we have that the current index's next doubling is over, so the correct block is in the current or next. Then the second loop moves it to the exact starting index of the block containing the position.
